track_notes: Not far from Menton or 3A2 land, it is a nice walk not too difficult, the path is good and as usual, you must have water if wx is warm, plenty room for antenna and also there is few building from world war 2.

This is a very long way to reach this summit!
You can come from the railway at Sospel (car park). get a lot of water in summertime (only one source). Enought room on summit for antenna
starting from Castillon, there is a large car park. the path is good
The trig point has moved!!! funny that nobody found the right place. I will check next time i go there from west crest.
track_title: Look like not the good track

track_notes:
This tracks provide access to the highest point (NO) of the Mont Razet compare to its twin (SE) that is 1m lower (yellow traces) :)
You can easly connect both top points via a small track.

From Baisse de Scuvion, heading SE and keep your head up to follow purple traces, keep them insight, you can always do some easy climb to reach the summit in case you loose the trace.

Finally the way back via the Pierre Pointu is longer but you can visit old Blockhaus ( and the white wall: an experimental acoustic observatory https://wikimaginot.eu/V70_construction_detail.php?id=16390 )
track_title: Mont Razet via two top points
